Retrieve lineups for a given NCAA game via its game_info_url

Source: R/ncaa_lineups.R
ncaa_lineups.Rd

Retrieve lineups for a given NCAA game via its game_info_url

Usage

ncaa_lineups(game_info_url = NULL, ...)

Arguments

game_info_url

The unique game info url

...

Additional arguments passed to an underlying function like httr.

Value

Returns a tibble of each school's starting lineup and starting pitcher

col_nametypes
yearnumeric
player_namecharacter
positioncharacter
slugcharacter
batting_ordercharacter
team_namecharacter
subnumeric
attendancecharacter
game_datecharacter
locationcharacter
player_idinteger
team_idnumeric
team_urlcharacter
conference_idnumeric
conferencecharacter
divisionnumeric
season_idnumeric

Examples

# \donttest{
  try(ncaa_lineups(game_info_url="https://stats.ncaa.org/contests/2167178/box_score"))
